# Framed Card Layouts

When building or updating any card-based layout, prefer framed card primitives from `@workspace/ui/components/card`.

- Use `CardFrame` as the parent container for grouped cards.
- Use `Card` children inside `CardFrame` instead of custom bordered wrappers.
- Use frame-specific slots (`CardFrameHeader`, `CardFrameTitle`, `CardFrameDescription`, `CardFrameAction`, `CardFrameFooter`) for shared frame-level content.
- Keep card internals on standard slots (`CardHeader`, `CardPanel`, `CardFooter`, `CardAction`), not custom div structures.
- Do not recreate framed visuals with ad-hoc classes (`border`, `rounded`, `shadow`, `divide-*`) when `CardFrame` primitives already cover the design.

## Preferred pattern

```tsx
<CardFrame>
  <Card>
    <CardHeader>
      <CardTitle>Overview</CardTitle>
    </CardHeader>
    <CardPanel>{/* content */}</CardPanel>
  </Card>

  <Card>
    <CardHeader>
      <CardTitle>Details</CardTitle>
    </CardHeader>
    <CardPanel>{/* content */}</CardPanel>
  </Card>
</CardFrame>
```
